11. O-O-O {Job achieved. The e-pawn is no longer defended and White's queen is tied down.} 
12. Bb2
12. Qc5 {We have a few possible options, but this is my favorite. We're getting ready to hop our knight into e3. Then it'll be impossible for White to castle on either flank.} 
13. Nc3 {White's sneaky idea is to meet13...Ne3with14.Na4.} 
13. Nf4 {But White has further weakened the e5-pawn.} 
14. Qe4
14. d5 {The classic counter to the queen on e4.} 
