11. g3 {The most natural. White wants to get castled.} 
11. Bb4 {But the problem of defending the pawns remains.} 
12. a3 {12.Bh3?fails to the pretty12...Qxc4!} 
12. Bxd2+
13. Bxd2
13. Ba6 {It won't be so easy to complete development.14.b3a4and the c-pawn remains weak.} 
14. Rc1
14. O-O {We're ready to hit the e-pawn.} 
15. Bh3
15. f5 {White is either going to have to retreat or simply sacrifice that c-pawn.} 
