11. h6 {The same concept.} 
12. Bh4
12. Qc7 {Fun but risky. If you want to keep things under control, then it's better to win the pawn with12...Bxc3and ...g7-g5. The assessment of both moves is 0.00, but this one is much wilder. See the main chapter for a deeper examination of this position.} 
