3. Qxd4 {The Center Game. When I lived in Italy, the coach at my local club was my good friend Riccardo Del Dotto. He loved the Center Game and even wrote a book on it.   Consequently, if you played 1...e5 you would reach this position. It's very aggressive. Unusually for 1.e4 e5 openings, White wants to castle queenside.} 
