1. e4
1. e5
2. Bc4 {I see this one is sometimes known as the Italian, although I think it's easier to consider that as the whole Bc4 complex. The vast majority of the time, White uses this move order simply to bypass the Petroff.} 
2. Nf6 {Here3.Nc3is a direct transposition to the Vienna and3.d4exd4is covered via 2.d4 in the Gambits Chapter.} 
