13. Ne5 {The only sensible continuation, but it doesn't work. Instead13.Be3Ne6!is just extremely comfortable. Next we'll capture on d7.} 
13. Bxe5 {I'm always reluctant to give up the fianchettoed bishop, but the rest of our pieces are about to become extremely active.} 
14. Rxe5
14. Nxd7 {Regaining the pawn and gaining a tempo on the rook. White is in trouble here, there's no time to develop their pieces.} 
15. Re1
15. Qh4 {Our plan is simple but brutal: ...Rfe8, ...Ne5 and then either to g4 and mate on h2 or f2 or into d3. It's surprising how big a problem the move c2-c3 turns out to be.} 
