11. exd6
11. O-O {While recapturing with11...Qxd6is probably also okay, this is much more in the right spirit. We sacrifice a pawn, but in return have two strong bishops on an open board and a lead in development.} 
12. d7 {I can see how this might be somewhat tempting. We cannot take the pawn immediately as our knight would be hanging, but the d-pawn is dropping very soon.} 
12. Nc5 {By moving the knight, we get ready to capture the pawn.12...Nd6is also pleasant.} 
13. Ne5 {The only sensible continuation, but it doesn't work. Instead13.Be3Ne6!is just extremely comfortable. Next we'll capture on d7.} 
13. Bxe5 {I'm always reluctant to give up the fianchettoed bishop, but the rest of our pieces are about to become extremely active.} 
