15. Re3
15. Ne5 {Exploiting White's back-rank issues.} 
16. Nd2 {Exchanging queens doesn't really help. We'll still rush to occupy the center.} 
16. Qd5 {The mate threat gains us another tempo.} 
17. Qf1
17. Rad8 {And next ...Rfe8 and ...f7-f5-f4, with absolute domination.} 
