13. Nd7 {Caruana's try the second time he reached this position. We target the d-pawn. This is stronger than damaging White's structure here, as, with White's knight already on g3, we cannot get subsequent control of the f4-square.} 
14. Bd5 {In the variation with12.Bc2we saw White try moving the bishopback to b3 with this intention. Here, though, it's much too risky.} 
14. Nxd4
15. Bxa8 {White doesn't have time to capture the rook.} 
15. Ne5 {Both White's queen and king are in peril. White's only move not to lose instantly is16.Re3, but then with16...Qxa8, we dominate the board for a tiny material investment.} 
16. Bd5 {It was too late for this bishop.} 
16. Nexf3+ {Capturing with the other knight first will come to the same thing.} 
17. gxf3
17. Nxf3+ {There's no way to keep both the king and queen.} 
18. Kh1 {Any other square would allow a discovered check.} 
18. Qh4 {But now White is just getting mated.} 
