22. Ne3
22. f5 {We carry out our break anyhow.} 
23. exf5
23. Nxf5
24. Nxf5
24. gxf5 {I agree we have an atrocious structure, but compare the relative activity of the pieces. We're ready to play ...Rac8-c2. White will have to develop their bishop at some point, and then both b2 and a3-pawns will fall.} 
