18. Rad1 {Bruzon Batista-Short, Ottawa 2013. Here Nigel played the logical18...Nc4, but I think it's more accurate to keep that in reserve. We don't want to make it so easy for White to exchange a pair of knights.} 
18. Rfe8 {Adding more pressure to the e-pawn. It's not at all clear what White should be doing here. We're pretty flexible. We can prepare the ...c7-c5 break or continue to attack the e-pawn with ...Qc6, while simply doubling rooks on the e-file is also useful.} 
