16. Na6 {White has to be careful with their queen, while the e-pawn remains a liability.} 
17. Qb3 {The queen retreat was tried in all three over-the-board games that reached this position.} 
17. Nc5 {Gaining another tempo.} 
18. Qc4
18. Qa4 {The counterintuitive queen exchange again. With the queens off the board we dominate the light squares.} 
19. e5 {The e-pawn is about to fall, so White may as well make this push.} 
19. Qxc4
20. Nxc4
20. dxe5
21. Nfxe5 {So far we've been following Patel-Betaneli, Saint Louis 2018. Black's choice of21...Nb3was fine, but let's recapture immediately.} 
21. Nxd5 {Our activity and strong bishop compensate for our slightly worse structure.} 
