25. Bxc4 {The final important move. We don't want to rush capturing the queen. That would at least allow White to develop their a1-rook. There's no time for that queen to hide, as we're threatening ...Ng2#.} 
26. Qxd8 {Or26.Bxc4Rxd1+followed by capturing on c4. White's king would still be in a lot of trouble. White's rooks cannot create any counterplay.} 
26. Ng2+ {We force the king to the d-file so that we can capture on d8 with a check. Material is still roughly level, with queen and pawn for the two rooks. If White could magically swap the king and a1-rook around, they'd be doing fine, but as is, White's lack of coordination will cost them the game.} 
