8. g5 {Even with c2-c3 included we can play this sharp path.8...Bg7would just revert to the usual lines after9.d4.I chose an additional path with8...Bh6!?exchanging dark-squared bishops. The opening experiment worked very well, but unfortunately, I squandered the game in time trouble.  We'll meet9.d4with9...g4.9.Nxg5walks into9...Rg8and ...h7-h6.   White could first exchange on c6, but the position remains extremely sharp. I don't think there's much value in memorizing much here, but if you're interested, then you'll find Stockfish a good sparring partner.} 
