5. d6 {Here I want to have a look at the hodgepodge of White's remaining options. I'll generally refrain from looking at White setups with d2-d3, as these will be covered in the d3-Spanish section.} 
6. c4 {We've already seen this idea with6.Re1Bd77.c4. We'll play in the same way.Finally6.Qe2, can be met with6...Bd7, when7.c3transposes to6.c3Bd77.Qe2, while6.d3is covered via5.d3d66.O-O.} 
