7. Bg7 {With a closed center,7...Bh6, with the idea of exchanging bishops, would be a great move. It's still interesting, but for now, I think we'd like to retain these bishops.} 
8. Nf1 {White continues their plan.8.O-Owill be covered via 7.O-O, while8.h3O-O9.Nf1will be covered shortly via the 9.h3 move order.} 
8. O-O {We want to open the center quickly, punishing White for delaying castling.} 
9. Ng3
9. d5 {Starting with9...b5is likely to come to the same thing, but we don't need it yet.} 
10. Qe2 {White doesn't want to allow the queens to be exchanged, but this is risky.} 
10. b5 {Once again White has the choice.} 
11. Bb3
11. Na5 {The addition of ...Na5 is always tricky to evaluate, but our plan becomes simple. We're going to push the c-pawn.} 
12. Bc2
12. dxe4 {Our plan is to block out the c2-bishop.} 
13. dxe4
13. Re8 {Let's first keep the e-pawn safely defended.} 
14. O-O
14. c5 {...c5-c4 is going to leave that bishop on c2 pretty demoralized.} 
