8. O-O {Now castling will transpose to7.O-OBg78.Be3O-O, analyzed shortly.} 
9. Nbd2 {White's argument is they want to develop the knight to g3 before castling, so the f1-square is available. We've seen the idea backfire before, but this time White has at least been able to develop their bishop.} 
9. Nd7 {But this is the problem. I mentioned previously that the e3-square is not a very reliable one for White. Our plan is to push the f-pawn, gaining time on the bishop in the process.   Just be careful not to allow White any tricks with Bb3+ and Ng5-e6. Therefore, we might play a preparatory ...Kh8 or ...Qe8 first.} 
10. O-O
10. Kh8 {The Spanish GM Miguel Santos Ruiz has been lucky enough to reach this position twice against an average rating just shy of 2700 (Ivanchuk and Nisipeanu). He made two comfortable draws.The plan of ...f7-f5 makes our position much easier to play. This time10...f5was also possible, but the position is incredibly murky after11.Bb3+Kh812.exf5gxf513.Ng5.} 
