10. Qe8 {As White's last cleared the way for the e3-bishop to retreat, the immediate10...f5would have been a big mistake. White gets there first with11.Bb3+Kh812.Ng5.But10...Kh8is also fine. As White's rook remains on the h-file,11.h4is actually the best move against both our tries. I think that's less obvious here with our king still on g8.} 
11. h4 {Not really in keeping with White's typical plan in the d3-Spanish, but the only way to hold the balance.} 
11. Nf6 {Returning now that White has weakened their kingside. We don't want to allow that pawn to get to h5.} 
12. Ng3
12. b5 {Or the immediate12...h5.} 
13. Bb3
13. h5 {Tkachenko-Rets, ICCF email 2019. We prevent the pawn from getting any further for good. The position is about equal, but I would prefer Black. I think we can make more use of g4 than White can of g5, especially with White's bishop liable to be hit. Our plan is the typical Chigorin rerouting with ...Na5 and ...c7-c5.} 
