10. g6 {The most ambitious. We keep material on the board. A good alternative is10...Nxb311.cxb3d5, when we immediately equalize.} 
11. Ba2 {Otherwise, we're ready to take. We delayed capturing so that White couldn't play d2-d4.} 
11. Bh6 {We'd like the dark-squared bishops off the board so White doesn't have the bishop pair advantage. In the resulting position, our knight is a good match for White's light-squared bishop.} 
