4. Ba4
4. Nf6
5. Qe2 {I believe this is officially known as the Wormald Attack, although in my brain I branch all these Qe2 setups as the Worrall. White's intention is to support the d2-d4 break by playing O-O, Rd1, and c2-c3. However, I believe the queen is generally misplaced on the e-file.Achieving the d2-d4 advance is tough, and even if they do, the e-pawn is likely to be very vulnerable. I'll be consistent and offer the unusual5...d6as our main approach, but I'll also briefly demonstrate a setup with the bishopon c5 as a straightforward alternative.} 
