13. Bxd7 {A shock, but it's just an exchange.} 
13. Bxd7
14. e6 {This pin is White's point.} 
14. Nxe6
15. Rxd7
15. Qe8 {We're following a game from the Patriarch: Botvinnik-Ragozin, Moscow 1946. White's rook looks powerful on the seventh, but ...Bd6 threatens to trap it, so it's forced to meekly retreat.} 
