4. dxc6 {The Exchange Spanish. White gives up the bishop pair for a slight lead in development and the nominally better structure. It used to be considered that Black had to be careful. White's plan is to exchange everything and win the king and pawn endgame. But the rise of the Berlin demonstrated that Black actually has little to fear in most endgames.} 
5. Nxe5
5. Qd4 {As explained in the Delayed Exchange positions, White wants to exchange their d-pawn for our one on e5, not the e-pawn. White no longer has dreams of a winning king and pawn endgame. By the way, d4 feels like the most forcing square, but5...Qe7does the same job.} 
