12. Qf3
12. Be6 {Solidly defending the pawn. Both Sethuraman's12...Qg6and Anton's12...Ng6!?pawn sacrifice are fine too.} 
13. Qe3
13. b6 {Just don't allow White's queen to land on a7.} 
14. f4
14. Bxb3 {Capturing before our bishop runs out of squares.} 
15. axb3
15. Kb7 {Lunek-Mirkowski, ICCF 2021. Our king is perfectly safe here. Our structure is by no means worse as long as we keep at least the queens or one pair of rooks on the board.} 
