18. Na3 {The Uzbek GM's attempt. The former FIDE World Champion has evidently studied this endgame in detail. He realizes that this is the best route. The knight is useful on c2. It controls the e1-square and so allows the white rook to activate without worrying about ...Re1+. The knight may want to later jump to d3.} 
