15. g4 {I would no longer play15...Bb4+since after16.Ke2, White is able to get the queens off, but we have lots of playable options. The curious15...Bh6!?has been the move in correspondence, but I'd prefer to keep control ofthe c5-square for now.15...d5also forces White to show incredible accuracy to hold equality. Our intention with15...g4is simply to defend theknight with ...Bh6.} 
