12. Be7 {We're just getting ready to castle. We can then defend the pawn with ...f7-f6. White's structure gives them some long-term compensation, but we don't need to worry. The c-pawn remains a bit of a nuisance for White. The natural way to defend it is with b2-b3, but then we can generate counterplay by pushing our a-pawn.} 
