4. Nxd4
4. Nf6 {In this chapter, we'll wrap up White's alternatives to going into the complexities of Mieses Variation (the proper Scotch). White's most serious move by far would be5.Nc3, but that is simply a direct transposition to the Scotch Four Knights covered elsewhere.} 
5. Nxc6 {The usual.} 
5. bxc6 {6.Nc3is an illogical move order. After6...Bb4, we'll be back in the Scotch Four Knights once again, while6...d5is a reasonable additional option.6.Bg5?!h6and6.f3?!d5fail the same way as they did on the previous move.} 
6. Bd3
6. d5 {The thematic continuation.} 
7. exd5 {White tends to immediately clarify the center.} 
7. cxd5
8. O-O {8.Bg5is also tried, but we can then develop our bishop more activelyto d6. We'll be in time to castle before White gets in Re1.} 
8. Be7 {Now that White was threatening a check we should develop our bishop more modestly. White now needs to decide on their plan. They can immediately fight for the center with9.c4, play slowly with a combinationof Nd2, b2-b3, Bb2, and h2-h3, or transpose to some sort of non-critical Four Knights with9.Nc3.} 
9. Nc3 {Starting with either9.Bf4or9.Bg5will come to the same thing after we castle, as White overwhelmingly opts to put their knighton c3. They could put it on d2, but our overall play remains the same.} 
9. O-O {We have a Scotch Four Knights with our bishop on e7 rather than b4. Seeing as Black often drops the bishop back willingly, we simply have an improved version.} 
10. Bf4
10. c5 {Time to grab some space.} 
11. Re1
11. Be6 {Our moves are all very natural.} 
12. Qf3
12. Bd6 {We challenge White's bishop so that we have access to the b-file. White should allow these bishops to be exchanged.} 
13. Bg5 {We don't need to worry about this exchange.} 
13. h6 {Please give us the bishop pair.} 
14. Bxf6
14. Qxf6 {With queens on the board we might be a bit scared of a kingside attack, but now White can make nothing of it.} 
15. Qxf6
15. gxf6 {We have the bishop pair and control of the center. In a pure Four Knights, White would have wanted to land their knight on f5 by now to force an exchange. Here we're not going to oblige.} 
