6. O-O
6. a5 {A few years ago, I was studying these positions in quite a lot of depth, as the Italian became my main opening. Black has many different setups, but this one seems quite straightforward. We give our bishop a retreat square and fight for possession of the queenside.  One key point is that we're almost always happy to offer an exchange of bishops with ...Be6. The structure after ...fxe6 can be a bit depressing if White can seize all the space on the queenside, but that's no longer possible.} 
