9. h3 {This subtlety appears to be White's best try. For now, the knight is needed on d2 to cover the e4-square.} 
9. Be6 {As we saw in the Spanish, White will probably need h2-h3 to prepare d3-d4. Otherwise, the pin with ...Bg4 will be very annoying. Here we don't need to worry about White's intricacies. We just continue with our plan.} 
10. Bxe6 {We're not concerned by the bishop exchange here either.} 
10. fxe6 {White has the typical problem of coming up with a plan. In the meantime, we have a kingside initiative.} 
11. Nf1
11. Nh5 {Our knight gets ready to hop into f4. Our queen will join in the fun from g6.} 
12. Be3 {White follows our example.} 
12. Nf4 {Next, we'll bring out queen round to g6.} 
