18. gxh3
18. Qxh3 {So we have two pawns for the piece and White's king is wide open. We have the brutal idea of ...Re6-g6. White's center is also loose. White is able to escape being mated, but not hold onto the center at the same time.} 
19. Re3 {The best try.19.Nh2is perhaps safer, but we can immediately restore material parity with19...Bxd4.} 
19. Qh5 {A final important move to remember. We get out of potential discovered knight jumps. We're ready to continue attacking with ...Re6 and ...Ng4. We can also play this quite slowly and go after the e-pawn by simply doubling on the e-file.} 
