6. Bb3 {The old school retreat. White is getting ready to drop the bishop back to c2. There are a lot of transpositions around here, but we'll focus on White delaying castling. If White switches plans and opts to move the king, then we'll invariably transpose to lines examined later in the chapter.} 
6. a5 {There's no reason for us to move away from our usual setup. Here though, we're unlikely to need to touch our bishop. White is never really ready to play d3-d4.} 
7. h3
