8. Nbd2 {8.O-Og5!?was our idea, although obviously, it's possible to play more calmly too.} 
8. Be6 {This will be our typical setup. With our pawn already on a5, we don't mind the doubled e-pawns. We're ready to challenge in the center with ...d6-d5.} 
