4. Bc5 {I've played quite a few Italians, or Giuoco Pianos, with both colors, but the move orders still confuse me. Still, I hope this repertoire will make sense. Against most setups, our next two moves will be ...d7-d6 and ...a7-a5.} 
5. c3
5. d6
6. b4 {Something a bit different, and another Jobava special. White expands before we've had time to play ...a7-a5, but it's double-edged.} 
6. Bb6
7. a4 {White doesn't have to play this immediately, although it's not really clear what they're doing otherwise.7.O-ONe7!?would likely transpose aftera subsequent a2-a4 and ...a7-a5. We could also keep our bishop with ...c7-c6.} 
