9. O-O
9. O-O {We'll play ...Ng6 and make sure to play ...c7-c6 before White is able to put a knight on c4. That way we can drop our bishop back to c7. We'll then play for the ...d6-d5 break. There's been quite a lot of action here, but I think we have straightforward equality.} 
