12. Nfd2
12. h5 {Grabbing space.} 
13. Nf1
13. d5 {Once White drops the knight back, we're ready to advance. White no longer has control of the e4-square.} 
14. exd5
14. Nxd5 {Our position is liberated. We're ready to meet Nfe3 with ...Nf4. We'll develop our queen and then castle queenside. White's in grave danger of being overrun.} 
