16. Qd7 {The e6-pawn is the important one to protect.} 
17. dxe4 {Not17.Qxb7?O-O. We would then threaten to trap the queen so it would have to beat a hasty retreat. We could then collect the d-pawn.} 
17. Nxe4 {So far we've been following the extremely well-played game Boskovic-Matlakov, Struga 2021. There Black played17...O-O-O, which is also fine, but I prefer grabbing the pawn.} 
