11. Nbd2
11. Qd8 {Returning to the ...b7-b6/b5 plan. White's queen is now misplaced. This plan isn't at all forced. We could also get on with our kingside play with11...Nh5, followedby ...Kh7 and ...f7-f5.12.Qd1would actually transpose back to the 8.O-O move order.} 
12. d4 {Thematic, but White struggles to hold onto that center.12.Qc2b5would be extremely similar to12.Qd1.} 
12. Nd7 {We attack the pawn. We're very happy to see13.d5. Then13...Ne7and we start King's Indianing itwith ...f7-f5.} 
