4. h6 {In the first two segments, we analyzed White's critical tries. Here I'll cover an eclectic assortment of other tries. We can generally decide whether to push the g-pawn one or two squares. White is just developing, not trying to refute our setup.} 
5. Be3 {Played an awful lot, but the bishop never really belongs here.} 
5. d5 {Simplest. We're going to hit both bishops.} 
6. exd5
6. Nxd5
7. Bxd5 {White's most common continuation, but giving up the light-squared bishop voluntarily is not a good idea.7.O-Ois better, but we're very comfortable after7...Be6. White would much prefer that bishop backon c1.} 
7. Qxd5
8. Nc3
8. Bb4 {When obliged we'll capture on c3, and then put White in another pin with ...Bg4.} 
