12. Nxa7 {This is the only way to let the queen out.} 
12. Nxa7 {An unusual imbalance. White has a rook and three pawns for the two pieces. A slight material advantage, and if White manages to sort out their pieces they'll be doing well, especially with those three connected passed pawns. But for now, both queen and king are under fire.  We'll coordinate with ...Nc6, ...Be7, ...Bb7, and ...O-O. With the knight hopping to d4 and the light-squared bishop eyeing the g2-pawn, White will be under a lot of pressure.} 
