19. Rf5 {Putting the rook on the fifth rank is once again the most tenacious. White wants to block the h-file with Rh5.} 
19. g6 {So we take the h5-square under control.20.Rh5is probably still White's best, but we just take it with a decisive advantage.} 
20. Rxa5 {Or20.Rf1g2, withmate on h2.} 
20. Qd4+
21. Kg2
21. Qf2 {White's extra three pieces are not particularly useful.} 
