[White "46) Forcing Italian 4.Ng5: White's other 8th moves"]
[Black "8.Be2 h6 9.Nf3 #19"]
[FEN "rnbqkbnr/pppppppp/8/8/8/8/PPPPPPPP/RNBQKBNR w KQkq - 0 1"]
[Result "*"]

1. e4
1. e5
2. Nf3
2. Nc6
3. Bc4
3. Nf6
4. Ng5
4. d5
5. exd5
5. Na5
6. Bb5+ {Overwhelmingly played. We just investigated White's dodgy alternatives.} 
6. c6 {The principal reaction. We make it a proper pawn sacrifice and damage our queenside into the bargain. But in return, White struggles to find a safe haven for their bishop.} 
7. dxc6
7. bxc6 {White has a wide choice. These days the odd looking8.Bd3is by far the most popular and was endorsed by both So and Krykun. We'll examine that next. The classical8.Be2is still seen from time to time, while the weird8.Qf3sees an occasional outing or two.} 
8. Be2 {The Classical main line. This is the most comfortable spot for the bishop but does leave the knight to fend for itself.} 
8. h6 {Now the knight is the problem. It lacks a good square.} 
9. Nf3 {The normal square, but White has gone off this in recent years.} 
9. e4 {The knight is forced to hop again.} 
10. Ne5
10. Bc5 {We play the same way. The threat of ...Qd4 is extremely awkward.10...Bd6is also promising.} 
11. c3 {This prevents our threat of ...Qd4, but it also creates additional weaknesses. The b1-knight is not at all happy. We're often able to exploit the loosening of the d3-square too.White sometimes tries11.f4?!too. That does defend the knight but leaves White's king stranded in the center. I think11...O-Ois easiest, with the idea of following upwith ...Nd5.} 
11. O-O {Our play here is nice and logical. All our pieces are going to control the center.} 
12. O-O
12. Qc7 {Not allowing that knight to catch its breath.} 
13. d4
13. exd3
14. Nxd3
14. Bd6 {Another threat. White still has too many problems to hope to convert their extra pawn. Our plan is to centralize our rooks.} 
15. g3
15. Bh3 {Developing with tempo.} 
16. Re1
16. Rad8 {Simple. ...Rfe8 will complete our development, and then ...c6-c5-c4 is a big threat. I really don't understand why anyone would willingly go for this variation. True, they're a pawn up, but White's position is just so miserable.} 
