13. Nxc4 {I suppose White is banking on the fact that their knight is no longer getting trapped, but exchanging the one defender of White's king for our offside knight is rather a promising trade.} 
14. Bxc4
14. Qh4 {White is forced to exchange on d5.} 
15. Bxd5+
15. cxd5 {A fantastic version of a Marshall Attack. White is not going to live long enough to convert their extra pawns.} 
16. g3
16. Qh3 {Now ...f5-f4 next move will decide.} 
17. f4
17. d4 {Opening the long diagonal.} 
18. Qf3
18. Rb8 {Soon the bishop will land, with painful consequences.} 
