7. dxc3 {Starting with7...Be6will come to the same thing.} 
8. Bxd5
8. Be6 {Simplest. We give back the piece to exchange queens and develop.} 
9. Bxe4 {9.Rxe4?White would prefer to keep the queens on the board. But9...Ne7wins at once. White's queen is undefended, and so the bishop drops for free.} 
9. Qxd1 {Off go the queens.} 
10. Rxd1
10. cxb2
11. Bxb2
11. f6 {We reach another position where White has insufficient play for the pawn. ... Bd6 and ...O-O-O looks like a promising plan.} 
