10. f5 {We force the rook to go passive. With our queen back on d8, White would have the powerful 11.Bh6, but here it doesn't work. After capturing the rook, our queen can slide out to g4.} 
11. Rf4
11. O-O {I lost this position as White in a blitz game against German GM Dmitrij Kollars. White is struggling with the misplaced rook and against the bishop pair.} 
