1. e4
1. e5
2. Nf3
2. Nc6
3. Nc3
3. Nf6
4. d4
4. exd4
5. Nd5 {The Belgrade Gambit.} 
5. Bc5 {The theoretical refutation is5...Nb4, exchanging White's active knight, but matters don't seem so clear to me. Let's develop and defend the d4-pawn instead.Note that6.Bc4will be simply met by6...h6defending the g5-square.With ...d7-d6 and ...O-O we'll emerge unscathed with our extra pawn.} 
6. Bg5 {The only way for White to maintain the balance.} 
6. Be7 {It's counterintuitive to move our bishop again, but White now needs to deal with the threat of capturing on d5.} 
7. Bf4 {Both sides lose a tempo with their bishop. We've now transposed to the old main line of5...Be7, but these days White tries6.Bd3there instead.} 
7. d6 {Parrying the threat to the c7-pawn.} 
8. Nxd4 {White has to recapture the pawn.8.Bb5is sometimes played but we can just castle out of the pin.} 
8. O-O {Taking on d5 is also fine, but this forces White to show accuracy to equalize. The e4-pawn is a pain to defend.} 
9. Nc3 {The best move, but this retreat suggests that the Belgrade Variation might not be that scary.} 
9. Bd7 {We have a few options here, but defending the knight keeps the most life in the game.9...Re8is also fine, while9...d5would force White to be accurate to hold equality.Our plan here is simply to put pressure on the e4-pawn with ...Re8 and ...Bf8. If White has to play f2-f3, then the central break ...d6-d5 nearly always works well. Putting the pawn on f3 creates a lot of weaknesses on the dark squares.} 
10. Nxc6 {White should probably exchange knights so that they can support the e-pawn more easily.} 
10. Bxc6 {We attack the e-pawn.} 
11. Bd3 {The point of the knight exchange.} 
11. Nd7 {With the e-pawn safely guarded, we'll change the plan a little. By moving the knight we free up the long diagonal for our bishop.} 
12. O-O
12. Bf6 {The position remains balanced, but I think we have more potential. We'll increase the pressure with ...Nc5, followed by expanding on the queenside. White still has some headaches holding on to the e4-pawn.} 
