13. Ba3 {White prevents us castling.} 
13. Kf7 {Our king is safe enough here. Next, we'll play ...d7-d5. White can play Bxc6 and Re1-e7+, but we're happy to give up our queen. In return, we'll have a rook and two pieces. Our control of the light squares prevents White from drumming up an attack.} 
