4. g6 {Against White's random flank pushes I think we can revert back to our fianchetto. We'll now reach very similar positions to those examined in 4.g3, but with colors reversed. If you recall, that was a reversed 4...h6 Italian, so this one is a 'reversed reversed Italian'. I guess that just makes it a 4...h6 Italian!Breaking in the center with4...d5always equalizes too. We'd just be playing a Four Knights Scotch as White.The extra a2-a3, a2-a4, or h2-h3 doesn't change very much. Just be a bit careful with4...Bc5, as White would then take theopportunity to capture on e5 and play d2-d4.} 
5. Nxe5 {The improved Halloween Gambit. This trick was the main reason I was trying 4.a3. I remember in a team event a certain Danish GM being so disgusted that I was playing like this and 'not taking it seriously' that he agreed on a quick draw against his much lower-rated opponent. I feel a bit vindicated that Stockfish considers it the best move...} 
