 {Of course, there can be nothing wrong with the Four Knights Variations. After all, the adage tells us to develop knights before bishops. But White does lose quite a bit of flexibility. The knight on c3 prevents White from supporting the d2-d4 break with c2-c3.Instead, they have two main approaches. We started with the more topical Scotch Four Knights. This has an extremely solid reputation and is often used at the top level to force a draw. Still, I hope my recommendation of8...Re8provides decent winning chances. Rather than immediately exchanging the central pawns we target White’se-pawn. White has to parry the threat of ...Bxc3 and ...Nxe4.  Against White’s less forcing moves, we’ll push our d-pawn one square, and then reroute our knight around to c5. We succeed in keeping a lot of tension in the position.9.Bg5is the most forcing approach.Here I suggest pushing ...d7-d5, but only after sidelining White’s dark-squared bishop. We’re preventing White from immediately liquidating with Qf3 and Bxf6. With our pawn on g5, our position is obviously a bit riskier than in the main lines, but we also have good chances to put White under pressure.We then moved on to the Spanish Four Knights. This is also known as a very solid variation.4...Bc5is the most combative approach. If White doesn’t act fast, we’ll exchange our worst knightwith ...Nd4. Our queenside play is then very straightforward. We should pay attention to White’s greedy attempts to grab the e-pawn. Our compensation is often based on an unpleasant pin along the d1-h5 diagonal.  White’s critical attempts are the temporary knight sacrifices with Nxe5. White erects a big center but has to be careful that the e4-square doesn’t become a big liability.The model game Wei Yi-Eljanov is a good demonstration of the strategic risks White is running.  We finished the segment examining White’s weird and wonderful alternatives on move four. With a symmetrical position, White can get away with a lot of waiting moves, but clearly, they don’t worry us. The Halloween Gambit with4.Nxe5?is fun, but clearly unsound.4.Bc4is the most natural development scheme, but here we have our temporary knight sacrifice with4...Nxe4!White is quickly on the back foot.} 1. --
