6. Bg7 {We saw that pushing the h-pawn just weakened White's king. But without it, it's difficult to see what White should do. We're ready to develop our knights.} 
7. Nc3
7. Nc6 {White has the same problems holding onto the d4-pawn.} 
8. Nd5 {Slow play with8.Qd3won't cut it. We can play8...Nge7and then just castle. White has nothing to show for the pawn.} 
8. Nce7 {That d5-knight is a strong centralized piece. Let's exchange it.} 
9. c3
9. Nxd5
10. Bxd5
10. Nf6 {We can afford to be greedy. We'll capture on d5 or e4 if the bishop retreats.} 
