11. Ke1 {Richard Rapport actually won this position with White quickly, but his opponent rushed.} 
11. g5 {Sethuraman's strong recommendation. We make sure the f4-pawn remains safe. The a8-knight is doomed. Once we capture it, we'll have two knights for rook and pawn. Rough material parity, but we have a sizeable advantage thanks to our more active pieces and lack of open files for the rooks.} 
