7. gxf3
7. Nd7 {If White challenges our queen, we'll drop it back to f6. We want to castle queenside, play ...g7-g5 to give our f-pawn more support and hop our kingside knight into play via e7 to f5. White's king has no safe haven, and the c1-bishop has its typical King's Gambit problem of being hemmed in by our f4-pawn.} 
