12. Ng4 {White has no minor pieces to defend on the kingside.} 
13. h3
13. Qh4 {White is powerless. Taking on e4 loses to ...Bh2+ and ...Nxf2. White has to sit and wait for us to crash through.} 
14. Nd2
14. Rae8 {We have a few plans: the simple ...f7-f5 is effective, while ...Nh2 followed by ...Nf3+ or ...Bxh3 is also mating.} 
