[Black "Remaining Gambits − Conclusion"]
[FEN "rnbqkbnr/pppppppp/8/8/8/8/PPPPPPPP/RNBQKBNR w KQkq - 0 1"]
[Result "*"]

 {The majority of this chapter was spent examining the Danish and Göring Gambits. I don’t believe the former is sound. With3...Qe7!we cause White a lot of problems. White loses the pawn but doesn’t get the kind of attacking compensation they were hoping for.  I believe the Göring Gambit to be sounder. One practical problem is that4...Nf6simply transposes to one of the main lines of the Ponziani. Our proposal of4...d5also appears challenging. With an accurate path of first developing the bishops, White struggles to get their king to safety, at least without exchanging queens. In the long run, White will have issues defending their isolated queen’s pawn.} 1. --
