3. Qxd4 {The Center Game.} 
3. Nc6 {The queen is forced to move again.} 
4. Qe3 {White normally opts for this square. At least it won't get hit immediately. But White will have further problems down the e-file.} 
4. Nf6 {Our play is very straightforward. We're going to pin the knight with ...Bb4, castle, and play ...Re8. White will have problems with the e-pawn.Despite over 4000 games in the online database, White hasn't really been able to find a good antidote.5.Bc4is covered in the Gambits Chapter.} 
5. Bd2 {A modern trend. White prevents the pin.} 
5. Be7 {So we'll develop more modestly. Now we threaten ...d7-d5.} 
6. c4 {White can prevent our break, but this form of Maroczy Bind has taken a lot of time to construct.} 
6. O-O
7. Nc3
7. Re8 {White is going to have to be really careful along the e-file.} 
8. O-O-O
8. Bb4 {We're attacking the e-pawn again. It's not clear that c2-c4 has helped White that much.} 
9. f3
9. d6 {We can no longer play ...d7-d5, but with ...Be6 and ...Ne5 we're ready to attack the new weakness on c4. White's king is not completely happy.} 
