[Black "Center Game − Conclusion"]
[FEN "rnbqkbnr/pppppppp/8/8/8/8/PPPPPPPP/RNBQKBNR w KQkq - 0 1"]
[Result "*"]

 {Recent years have not been kind to the Center Game. It’s a refreshing approach, with White aspiring to attack like some sort of Open Sicilian, but the e-pawn is too large a weakness.As long as we’re aware of a few nuances such as10...Be7!, and the idea of sacrificing the exchange to neutralize White’s initiative, then I think we can be extremely confident.  Perhaps White’s best is a fifth-move alternative like5.Bd2, but if we get to breakwith ...d7-d5, then we have zero problems.  These days it’s extremely rarely seen in anything but blitz chess. Our play is logical. White has been unable to even find lines that force us to demonstrate accurate defense.} 1. --
