 {There’s very little we need to know in this chapter.1.e4e52.Bc4is a serious move, but the theoretical routes involve transposing to either the Italian or the Vienna. We may as well know a bit about3.f4?!there, but I think the refutation is fairly logical.  Most of the remainder of the chapter sees White play reversed openings. With the extra tempo they generally equalize, but they don’t put any pressure on our position at all. We’re extremely flexible. Taking control of the center, followed by putting the bishop on d6 makes a lot of sense.  With that, I wish you the very best in your endeavors. And I hope you’ve enjoyed the course!} 1. --
